                TOP







二





 
簡介 
  | 招生方式 | 課表 | 
  學分總表 | 中英文課程綱要

授課計畫表|招生考試考古題|碩博士班



民法債編總論　
法碩專二 必　（3—3）
本課程之開設，係為指導學生認識民法債編通則章(第一五三條至第三四四條)之規定內容，就債權債務法律關係之發生原因、內容、效力、變更及消滅，為細膩之法律分析，並引導其於具體案例中，正確適用相關之規定。本課程所教授之範圍包括：債之發生、債之標的、債之效力、多數債權人與債務人、債之移轉、債之消滅。本課程之教學目標，除引導學生正確認識上述法律關係，訓練其處理相關法律爭端之思惟能力外，亦在啟發其對法治社會之使命感及研究之興趣。

CIVIL LAW: GENERAL PROVISIONS 
    OF OBLIGATIONS
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    (3 – 3 )
The course is designed to help 
    students understand the principles provided in “General Provisions of Obligations” 
    Part of the ROC Civil Code (art. 153-344), and analyze the beginnings of obligatory 
    relationships, the contents of obligations, together with their effects, transfer 
    and extinction. The topics included in this course are sources of obligations, 
    object of obligations, effects of obligations, joint creditors and debtors, 
    transfer of obligations, and extinction of obligations. Besides their correct 
    application of such rules in specific cases, it is also anticipated that the 
    students be equipped with the capability to resolve related legal disputes 
    and be inspired to commit to society with rule of law.
　

民法債編各論　
法碩專二 必（2—2）
本課程之開設，係為指導學生認識民法債編「各種之債」章(第三四五條至第七五六條)之規定內容。本課程所教授之範圍包括：買賣、互易、交互計算、贈與、租賃、借貸、僱傭、承攬、出版、委任、經理人及代辦商、居間、行紀、寄託、倉庫、運送營業、承攬運送、合夥、隱名合夥、指示證券、無記名證券、終身定期金、和解、保證。本課程之教學目標，除引導學生正確認識上述法律關係，訓練其處理法律爭端之思惟能力外，亦在啟發其對法治社會之使命感及研究之興趣。

CIVIL LAW: KINDS OF OBLIGATIONS
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    ( 2- 2 )
“CIVIL LAW: KINDS OF OBLIGATIONS” 
    is designed to help students understand the principles provided in “Particular 
    Kinds of Obligations” Part of the ROC Civil Code (art. 345-756). The topics 
    included in this course are: sales, barter, account stated, gift, lease, loan, 
    hire for use, hire for work, indepondent contractor’s undertaking, publication, 
    mandate, manager and commercial agents, brokerage, commission agency, boilment, 
    warehousing, carriage, forwarding agency, partnership, sleeping partnership, 
    orders of payment, obligations to bearers, life annuity, compromise, and suretyship. 
    Besides their correct application of such rules in specific cases, it is also 
    anticipated that the students be equipped with the capability to resolve related 
    legal disputes and be inspired to commit to society with rule of law.

民法物權

法碩專二　必　（2—2）
本課程之開設，係為指導學生認識民法物權編(第七五七條至第九六六條)所規定之法律關係，區辨其與債權債務法律關係之差異，並引導其於具體案例中，正確適用相關之規定。本課程所教授之範圍包括：物權通則、所有權、地上權、永佃權、地役權、抵押權、質權、典權、留置權及占有。本課程之教學目標，除引導學生正確認識上述法律關係，訓練其處理法律爭端之思惟能力外，亦在培養其進一步研究相關問題之興趣。

CIVIL LAW: PROPERTY
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    (2 – 2 )
The course is designed to help 
    students understand the legal relationships provided in “Property” Part of 
    the ROC Civil Code (art. 757-966), and apply related rules correctly in specific 
    cases. The topics included in this course are general principles, ownership, 
    superficies, yung-tien(farm land tenancy for life), servitude, mortgages, 
    pledges, dine, retention, and possession. Besides their correct understanding 
    such relationships, it is also anticipated that the students be equipped with 
    the capability to resolve the legal disputes regarding property and be interested 
    in related researches.
　

刑法分則

法碩專二　必　（2—2）
刑法分則（性質上為「刑法各論」）係以刑法典上之「刑法分則」（第一○○條至第三五七條）為主要對象，研究各種類型之犯罪與相對應之刑罰；
刑法各論係研究各種犯罪本身之學問，探討刑法規定各種犯罪其立法上所要保護之法益為何、須具備那些要件（要素）及其與「刑法總論」之相互關連性。
由於「刑法各論」較註重各個犯罪本身所存在之個別問題，故判例、解釋等實務見解成為重要參考內容。如何使二年級學生瞭解各個犯罪本身之個別問題、實務見解以及如何與「刑法總論」相配合，乃本階段之主要任務。

CRIMINAL LAW: KINDS OF CRIME
Special LL.M. second-year (2 
    – 2 )

This course will cover 
    the specific offenses in Criminal Code（Articles 100-357） and study the various 
    types of criminal offenses and their respective penalties.

In other words, this course 
    is to study the offenses, including the components of the crimes, legal interests 
    to be protected and the connection between the specific offenses and the General 
    Principles of Criminal Code.

Since the Criminal 
    Code－Specific Offenses will focus on the issues associated with individual 
    crimes, the court decisions and interpretations will be important reference 
    materials. The goal of this course is to train the second-year law students 
    to understand the issues associated with such individual crimes, the court’s 
    view on such crimes and how the theory is reconciled with the General Principles 
    of the Criminal Code.

　

刑事訴訟法　
法碩專二 必（2—2）
刑事訴訟法是規範刑事訴訟程序的法規，遇有具體犯罪發生時，研究如何依刑事訴訟法所規定之訴訟程序，對該行為人的犯罪事實，追訴、處罰，據以確定國傢具體的刑罰權，追求實體的真實發現，重視程序的公正維持，藉以保障個人自由、維護社會安全，所以本課程之進行，兼顧基本理論架構之建立及司法判解實例之分析，以現行刑事訴訟為經，以司法判解實務為緯，探討法理，分析實例，綜合研析刑事訴訟法學，俾利啟發學習興趣，訓練思考研究，培養深入研究能力，充實同學法律生活化之內涵。

CRIMINAL PROCEDURE
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    ( 2 – 2 )
An analysis of the legal and 
    practical problems presented in the administration of criminal justice from 
    the point of criminal investigation to post-conviction review, mainly based 
    upon the provisions of Code of Criminal Procedure. It covers the following 
    subjects: Fundamentals of Criminal Procedure, Court Jurisdiction, Service 
    of Process, Arrest, Booking, Search and Seizure, Inquisition of the Accused, 
    Examination of Witness, the Pre-trial Stage: the Indictment, the Trial, Appeal, 
    Execution, Re-trial and Extra-ordinary Appeal, Summary Trial Process, Attendant 
    Damages Claim, etc.
　

行政法
法碩專二 必（2—2）
行政法課程主要包含：1.行政法之理論基礎，此涉及行政及行政法之概念，行政法之法源等；2.行政組織，此涉及行政機關、公務員及公物等；3.行政作用，此以行政命令、行政處分、行政契約等為主；4.行政救濟及國家責任。

ADMINISTRATIVE LAW
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    ( 2- 2 )
The main topics of this course 
    include 1.basic theories of administrative law, concerning the concept of 
    government administration and administrative law, the source of administrative 
    law, etc. 2. Administrative organizations, concerning administrative institutions, 
    public officials, public property, etc, 3. Administrative functions, mainly 
    covering administrative ordinance, administrative measures, administrative 
    contracts, and 4. Administrative remedies and state liabilities.
　

研究方法及法律文件寫作

法碩專二 必（1—1）
本課程之目的在使學生熟悉英文法律文件的寫作。導論部分講授基本理論，介紹撰寫法律文件必須具備的原則。其餘介紹二十幾種法律文書範例，藉以分析其基本法律關係，使學生能將所學之法律理論實際應用於法律實務工作。
本課程上課以英語講授，俾使熟悉英文法律用語及意見之表達方式並介紹英美法與大陸法有關法律文件寫作上不同之處。

RESEARCH METHOD AND LEGAL WRITING

special ll.m. second-year 
    required（1—1）

This course is designed to initiate 
    the students into the practical application of legal knowledge in the drafting 
    of legal documentation. This course devotes the beginning sessions to a general 
    discussion in basic theories of legal writing. It then progresses into analysis 
    of some 25 different documents commonly seen in legal practice. As the documents 
    discussed are in English, we also take the opportunity to familiarize the 
    students with English legal terms, as well as to make a comparative study 
    of legal writing under different legal systems.
　

海商法
法碩專二 必
（2—0）
自海牙規則生效後，海事法歷經數十年的發展，其間雖再有漢堡規則的提出，然則隨科技之進步及海事仲裁之盛行，原依傳統法制結構來處理海事糾紛的方式已然有所變更。有鑑於此，本課程之主要內容係以下幾大部分為主：
（１）海事法之定義及其與海商法之關係；
（２）海事法在國際運送發展中之地位；
（３）以海上運送為中心探討我國海商法之人、事、物等概念之定義；
（４）以海牙規則建構之舉証責任體系為中心，探討海商相關問題；
（５）共同海損、海難救助及其相關國際公約或協定之探討；
（６）簡介海事法之發展（含海上保險、國際管轄等課程）

MARITIME LAW
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    ( 2 – 0 )
For years, while there is a 
    newly proposed Hamburger Rule, the development of maritime laws mainly follow 
    the evolutionary pace of Hague Rules.
However, the fast development 
    of technology and widely adoption of maritime arbitration in the maritime 
    industry has significantly affected the traditional legal structure of proceeding 
    the maritime disputes.
The followings are the maritime 
    subjects to be covered:
The definition of Maritime Law 
    and its relation with the Admiralty Law.
The role of maritime law in 
    the development of international transportation of goods.
The definition of Person, Matter, 
    Res and etc. subject to the core study of maritime transportation issues.
The burden of proof under Hague 
    Rules and Admiralty related issues.
The studies on the international 
    conventions or treaties regarding general loss, maritime salvage and etc.
A concise to the development 
    of maritime law (including maritime insurance, international jurisdiction 
    and etc.)
　

英美侵權行為法專題研究

法碩專二 必　（2—0）
希藉英美法院案件解析與相關資料研讀，培養學生法學上思考、分析及判斷能力，瞭解英美侵權行為法律體系及其應用；內容包括：侵權行為民事責任沿革、故意侵權行為、過失侵權行為、因果關係、共同侵權行為、限制性侵權責任、土地所有/占有人責任、嚴格責任、產品責任、誹謗、濫訴、不實陳述、新型態侵權行為、抗辯事由、損害賠償及其他救濟途徑等。本課程之教學並採取與我國民法相關規定為比較法研討，得以俾益學生於我國法律之學習。

ANGLO-AMERICAN LAW OF TORT
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    ( 2 – 0 )
This course is to use the leading 
    and teachable Anglo-American Torts cases and various legal materials for the 
    students to understand the contemporary law of Torts and incipient trends. 
    The fundamentals that the course offered include the followings: development 
    of tort liability, intentional torts, negligence, causation, joint tortfeasors, 
    limited duty, tortuous liability of owner and occupiers of land, defense, 
    strict liability, products liability, defamation, misuse of legal procedure, 
    misrepresentation, interference with advantageous relationships and damages. 
    For purpose of comparative legal studies, the students are encouraged to take 
    the related provisions of Chinese civil code into comparison.
　
　

保險法

法碩專二 必
（0—2）
保險法以契約法為主，業法為輔。兼及大陸地區保險法規，英美德諸國立法例，及強制汽車責任保險法，授課內容為：

1.保險契約及其性質。

2.保險利益。

3.保險費。

4.危險之確定與控制。

5.損害填補與代位。

6.保險契約之內容與分類。

7.保險契約效力之變動。

8.保險人與要保人之權義。

9.財產保險與人身保險在性質上
之差異。

INSURANCE LAW
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    (0 – 2 )
The course covers the following 
    topics:
1.Insurance contract and policy.
2.Insurable interest and insurance 
    proceeds.
3.Premium and rating.
4.Control and Ascertaining.
5.Principle of Indemnity and 
    subrogation.
6.The clause of Insurance and 
    its contents.
7.Validity of Insurance.
8.Rights and duties of the Insurer 
    and the insured.
9.The differences between Life 
    and Non-life Insurance.
　
　

英美契約法專題研究

法碩專二 必
（0—2）
希藉英美法院案例解析與相關資料研讀，培養學生思考契約問題與正確解決問題之方法，進而提升法學上思考、分析及判斷能力，瞭解英美契約法體系及統一商法典第二章買賣法；本課程內容包括：契約自由原則、契約之成立、要約承諾之機制、準契約及事實上契約、約因、契約之履行、契約之解釋及顯失公平、違約及其救濟、契約債權債務之轉移、第三人利益契約、誠信原則、口頭證據法則、實質履行法則、條件與期前拒絕履行等。本課程並採取與我國民法相關規定為比較法研討，得以俾益學生於我國法律之學習。

ANGLO-AMERICAN LAW OF CONTRACTS
Special LL.M. second-year required 
    ( 0 – 2 )
The underlying purpose of this 
    course is to teach the students to consider the possible ways of handling 
    contract problems, and to choose the right way of solving legal problems. 
    Leading cases and materials are used as the learning tool to enhance the thinking 
    and analyzing abilities, and to understand the American contract law, which 
    includes the Article two of the Uniform Commercial Code. The fundamentals 
    that the course offered include the following: consideration, bargain principle, 
    remedies, offer and acceptance, quasi-contract and implied-in-fact contracts, 
    bargain in good faith, the parole evidence rule, course of performance, assignment, 
    interpretation and unconsionability, mistake, changed circumstances, third 
    party beneficiaries, performance in good faith, the doctrine of substantial 
    performance, express conditions, breach and anticipatory repudiation, etc. 
    The comparative legal studies are also encouraged in this course, the students 
    may take the related Chinese Civil Code into comparison.
　
　

　 



